Haas' German driver Mick Schumacher is out of the Saudi Arabia Formula One Grand Prix after a high-speed crash. AFP/Andrej Isakovic JEDDAH - Mick Schumacher insisted Saturday 'I'm OK' but he will not take part in Sunday's Saudi Arabian Grand Prix after crashing his Haas car at 240km/h in qualifying on Jeddah's high-speed street circuit. "Hi everyone, I just wanted to say that I'm ok. Thank you for the kind messages. The car felt great @HaasF1Team, we'll come back stronger," tweeted the 23-year-old German driver who was airlifted to hospital after the crash. Hi everyone, I just wanted to say that I‚Äôm oküôè
